# Iron Agent Protocol

Use `AGENTS.md` as the top-level contract.

Iron Agent stores accumulated prompts, rules, SOPs, and preferences to reduce
tokens and personalize model behavior.

Memory/rules must be routed by script before reading files:

```bash
python system/scripts/memory_router.py --task "<task>"
```

If paths are returned, read only those paths and apply their prompts/rules as an
overlay to the user's request. If no paths are returned, treat the request as
new content and continue normally.

Keep directory files route-only and low-token. Move details to leaf files.

Ask before destructive changes, external effects, or secret handling.
Log useful prompt/rule/SOP candidates for nightly maintenance when practical.
